[2] Cholera - Tanzania (Mwanza Region)
Date: Mon 7 Dec 2015
Source: Daily News [edited]
http://www.dailynews.co.tz/index.php/home-news/44868-cholera-kills-19-in-mwanza

19 patients out of 613 who were suffering from cholera in Mwanza region and who were admitted have died of the epidemic that has engulfed the region in the last 3 months, the region administration has said. Speaking during the weekend in Mwanza City, Mwanza Regional Commissioner (RC) Mr Magesa Mulongo said the deaths are a blow to the region. He directed all city workers, ward executive officers and health officers to keep the city environment in a sanitary condition in order to contain the epidemic.

"So far the number of people suffering from cholera is 613, of which 263 are from Ukerewe, 180 from Ilemela, Sengerema (135), Nyamagana (29) and Magu (6)," he said.

"The level of how we lost our brothers and sisters has shocked us. The 19 people who died of the disease are simply too many. Let us put more efforts in the fight against cholera because we had the president's instructions which required us to improve sanitation in our region when commemorating Uhuru day in order to control the disease."

[Byline: Nashon Kennedy]

