[3] Cholera - Uganda (Kampala)
Date: Sun 6 Dec 2015
Source: The Observer [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201512071388.html

6 people have died of cholera, while 21 others are being treated at the isolation ward set-up at Mulago hospital. According to Ministry of health permanent secretary Dr Asuman Lukwago, since November 2015, when the isolation unit was set up, 6 deaths have so far been recorded.

The infectious disease caused by consumption of contaminated food or water has spread to 5 other districts across the country, with over 50 cases diagnosed since the 1st outbreak was reported in October 2015 in Busia. The health ministry recently announced that it had contained the outbreak in Busia, but it seems the El Nino rains have hindered their progress, causing flooding and worsening the hygiene situation.

The reported cases are from Kampala slums of Katanga, Kyebando while others were referrals from other districts. Lukwago says more cases have been confirmed in Hoima, Kasese, Busia and Wakiso.

