[4] Cholera - Uganda (Mbale District)
Date: Thu 10 Dec 2015
Source: The Monitor [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201512100980.html

Mbale District leaders have ordered the closure of all eating places that do not meet minimum health standards following a cholera outbreak that has left 12 people admitted to treatment centres. The outbreak comes at a time when the district is experiencing heavy El Nino rain, coupled with poor drainage.

The acting district health officer, Dr Jonathan Wangisi, told Daily Monitor on 8 Dec 2015 that about 12 people have been admitted and the district health technical team has already issued warnings to people to stop buying food and drinks sold on the streets in Mbale suburbs, in order to curb further spread of the disease.

The cholera epidemic victims have been admitted to Namanyonyi Health Centre 111 and Namatala Health Centre 1V in critical condition.

"It's true there has been an outbreak of cholera in the district. 12 suspected cases have been detected in Namanyonyi Sub-county and Industrial Division in Mbale Municipality. Of the 6 samples that were taken, 1 has been confirmed positive," Dr Wangisi said.

[Byline: Mudangha Kolyangha and Olivier Mukaaya]

