[5] Cholera - Uganda (Wakiso District)
Date: Tue 8 Dec 2015
Source: New Vision [edited]
http://www.newvision.co.ug/news/676636-seven-killed-as-cholera-breaks-out-in-wakiso.html

7 people have been confirmed dead and 20 others hospitalized as cholera breaks out in Wakiso district. Dr. Robert Kagwire, the district acting health officer, said the epidemic struck parts of Kitufu and Zinga Islands in Bussi Sub county, Masulita town and Nabweru in Nansana Municipality.

He said the dead included a 1-year-old boy and his mother. Kagwire said they died 2 weeks ago and that the 1st person to die was in Masulita Sub-county and others were on the Islands.

During a tour, Kagwire said they also heard that 67 people had reported to different health centres in the areas with signs and symptoms associated with cholera. "2 weeks ago we got complaints from Nabweru where a child was rushed to the Nabweru health centre IV. She was treated and she is okay. So we have managed to treat a number of them although 20 are still admitted at different health centres on the Islands," he said.

He said they were monitoring the situation closely to prevent the disease from spreading.

[Byline: Andrew Ssenyonga]

